profile_positions.description:
Current Tasks and Responsibilities (Faculty Coordinator, (approx.0,8 fte):
•	Coordinate the syllabus approval process;
•	Enter student grades into the system and provide faculty with grading deadlines;
•	Provide on-going support to faculty and organize faculty meetings;
•	Provide faculty contracts;
•	Schedule courses;
•	Enter course information into database;
•	Enter student and faculty evaluation forms into database and distribute them to Heads of 
        Department;
•	Manage database of taught classes, faculty qualifications, directed studies and internships;
•	Take minutes at Academic and Exam Board meetings;
•	Support the Exam Office to register and archive student papers;
•	Assist with assessment processes for accreditation purposes.

Current Tasks and Responsibilities (Site Registrar, approx. 0,2 fte):
•	Supply student proof or enrollment letters and processing transcript requests;
•	Liaising with IB/DUO Group for students enrolled in Webster's Dutch Accredited programs;
•	Monitor grades for certificate programs, gather reports from instructors and issue certificates;
•	Provide attendance lists;
•	Manage database of course registrations;
•	Provide duplicate and notarized copies of diplomas to the students;
•	Support the local Exam Board;
•	Archive files for alumni and quits.

Main tasks and responsibilities:
- Providing editorial assistance to the Executive Editor in his day-to-day work and pointing out    
     relevant deadlines;
- Scheduling and coordinating meetings with the Executive Editor and the Associate Editors;
- Handling all incoming electronic correspondence sent to the journal’s editorial office;
- Managing and updating the journal’s offline database and online electronic submission system;
- Maintaining an effective filing system for all articles submitted to the journal (about 300     
     submissions per year);
- Communicating professionally with authors (about 300 per year) and reviewers (about 900 per     
     year) from all over the world and solving all their queries;
- Maintaining excellent relationships with management and external departments (publishing   
     department, technical department) and ensuring smooth communication;
- Preparing annual statistical reports on the journal’s citation data with reference to the main 
     international bibliometric databases.
